  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 53 g
  sodium: 3 g
---

Pop a large #pot{} of water on to boil with a @salt{pinch}. Chop the @British chicken breasts{3} into 2cm chunks.

Put a #frying pan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Once the pan gets hot, add your chicken along with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a grind of @black pepper{grind}. Cook for ~{6-8%minutes} until your chicken is nicely browned.

Cut off the root and leafy part from the @leek{2}. Cut in half lengthways, then slice into thin half moon shapes. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(grated). Separate the @basil{1}(finely chopped) leaves and stalks and finely chop the stalks and tear the leaves in half. Chop the @sundried tomatoes{40g} into small ½cm pieces.

Once your chicken is nicely browned, add your leek and sun-dried tomatoes. Cook for another ~{5%minutes}, then add your basil stalks and half your garlic. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pop the @fusilli{400g} into the boiling water and cook for ~{9%minutes} or until 'al dente'. Once cooked, drain your pasta.

> 'Al dente' means the pasta is cooked through but has a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle - if it's not quite there yet, just cook for a little longer.

Add the @creme fraiche{1}, @chicken stock pot{1} and @water{200ml} to your leek mixture. Stir well to dissolve your stock pot, bring to a gentle simmer and cook for ~{5%minutes}. While your sauce is cooking, chop any tough bottom from the root end of the @kalettes{1}(cut in half).

> Just like you would with brussels sprouts!

Once drained, pop your pasta into an #ovenproof dish{}. Add your sauce and stir together. Mix the @panko breadcrumbs{30g}, @grated hard Italian style cheese{40g} and @poppy seeds{2} with the @olive oil{3%tbsp} and a good grind of @black pepper{grind}, and sprinkle this over your pasta.

Preheat your #grill{} to high and pop your dish under for ~{4-5%minutes} or until the topping is golden brown.

Meanwhile, wash your frying pan and put it on medium heat with the @Netherend butter salted{30g}. Once your butter has melted, add your kalettes along with a splash of @water{splash} and a grind of @black pepper{grind}. Cook for ~{5-6%minutes}, then add your remaining garlic and cook for a further ~{1%minute}.

Serve your pasta bake in #bowls{} with your kalettes and basil on top. Enjoy!